<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 13 at 1:32AM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Periods of light snow expected through Monday morning...
Weak disturbances within a southwesterly flow aloft will bring
periods of light snow through Monday morning over Lewis and
Clark, Jefferson, and Broadwater counties.
Snowfall amounts will range from a dusting to a half inch over
the lower elevations to as much as two inches over the mountain
passes.
Impacts will include visibility down to one mile and slippery
road conditions. Some impacted areas include the city of Helena,
Interstate 15 from Butte to Helena, Highway 12 from MacDonald Pass
to Toston, and Highway 200 from Roger`s Pass to Bowman`s Corner.
Use caution if traveling tonight or Monday morning.</description>
